g="H6908">together</char>, there <char style="w" strong="H6485">lacked</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1732">David’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char> <char style="w" strong="H8672">nineteen</char> <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> and <char style="w" strong="H6214">Asahel</char>. <verse eid="2SA 2:30" /><verse number="31" style="v" sid="2SA 2:31" />But the <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> had <char style="w" strong="H5221">smitten</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1144">Benjamin</char>, and of <char style="w" strong="H0074">Abner’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H0582">men</char>, <char style="add">so that</char> <char style="w" strong="H7969">three</char> <char style="w" strong="H3967">hundred</char> and <char style="w" strong="H8346">threescore</char> <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> <char style="w" strong="H4191">died</char>.<verse eid="2SA 2:31" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="32" style="v" sid="2SA 2:32" />¶ And they took <char style="w" strong="H5375">up</char> <char style="w" strong="H6214">Asahel</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H6912">buried</char> him in the <char style="w" strong="H6913">sepulchre</char> of his <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char>, which <char style="add">was in</char> <char style="w" strong="H1035">Beth-lehem</char>. And <char style="w" strong="H3097">Joab</char> and his <char style="w" strong="H0582">men</char> <char style="w" strong="H3212">went</char> all <char style="w" strong="H3915">night</char>, and they came to <char style="w" strong="H2275">Hebron</char> at break of <char style="w" strong="H0215">day</char>.<verse eid="2SA 2:32" /></para>
