n</char>. <verse eid="2SA 3:35" /><verse number="36" style="v" sid="2SA 3:36" />And all the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> took <char style="w" strong="H5234">notice</char> <char style="add">of it</char>, and it <char style="w" strong="H3190">pleased</char> them: as whatsoever the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="w" strong="H6213">did</char> <char style="w" strong="H5869">pleased</char> all the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3.36 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">pleased them: Heb. was good in their eyes</char></note> <verse eid="2SA 3:36" /><verse number="37" style="v" sid="2SA 3:37" />For all the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> and all <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> <char style="w" strong="H3045">understood</char> that <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> that it was not of the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> to <char style="w" strong="H4191">slay</char> <char style="w" strong="H0074">Abner</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H5369">Ner</char>. <verse eid="2SA 3:37" /><verse number="38" style="v" sid="2SA 3:38" />And the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto his <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char>, <char style="w" strong="H3045">Know</char> ye not that there is a <char style="w" strong="H8269">prince</char> and a great <char style="w" strong="H1419">man</char> <char style="w" strong="H5307">fallen</char> this <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> in <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>? <verse eid="2SA 3:38" /><verse number="39" style="v" sid="2SA 3:39" />And I <char style="add">am</char> this <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> <char style="w" strong="H7390">weak</char>, though <char style="w" strong="H4886">anointed</char> <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>; and these <char style="w" strong="H0582">men</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1121">sons</char> of <char style="w" strong="H6870">Zeruiah</char> <char style="add">be</char> too <char style="w" strong="H7186">hard</char> for me: the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> shall <char style="w" strong="H7999">reward</char> the doer of <char style="w" strong="H6213">evil</char> according to his <char style="w" strong="H7451">wickedness</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">3.39 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">weak: Heb. tender</char></note><verse eid="2SA 3:39" /></para>
