style="w" strong="H1664">Gittaim</char>, and were <char style="w" strong="H1481">sojourners</char> there until this <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char>.) <verse eid="2SA 4:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="2SA 4:4" />And <char style="w" strong="H3083">Jonathan</char>, <char style="w" strong="H7586">Saul’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char>, had a <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> <char style="add">that was</char> <char style="w" strong="H5223">lame</char> of <char style="add">his</char> <char style="w" strong="H7272">feet</char>. He was <char style="w" strong="H2568">five</char> <char style="w" strong="H8141">years</char> <char style="w" strong="H1121">old</char> when the <char style="w" strong="H8052">tidings</char> <char style="w" strong="H0935">came</char> of <char style="w" strong="H7586">Saul</char> and <char style="w" strong="H3083">Jonathan</char> out of <char style="w" strong="H3157">Jezreel</char>, and his <char style="w" strong="H0539">nurse</char> took him <char style="w" strong="H5375">up</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H5127">fled</char>: and it came to pass, as she made <char style="w" strong="H2648">haste</char> to <char style="w" strong="H5127">flee</char>, that he <char style="w" strong="H5307">fell</char>, and became <char style="w" strong="H6452">lame</char>. And his <char style="w" strong="H8034">name</char> <char style="add">was</char> <char style="w" strong="H4648">Mephibosheth</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.4 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Mephibosheth: or, Merib-baal</char></note> <verse eid="2SA 4:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="2SA 4:5" />And the <char style="w" strong="H1121">sons</char> of <char style="w" strong="H7417">Rimmon</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0886">Beerothite</char>, <char style="w" strong="H7394">Rechab</char> and <char style="w" strong="H1196">Baanah</char>, <char style="w" strong="H3212">went</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H0