  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="2SA 10:1" />And it came to pass after <char style="w" strong="H0310">this</char>, that the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H1121">children</char> of <char style="w" strong="H5983">Ammon</char> <char style="w" strong="H4191">died</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H2586">Hanun</char> his <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> <char style="w" strong="H4427">reigned</char> in his stead. <verse eid="2SA 10:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="2SA 10:2" />Then <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char>, I will <char style="w" strong="H6213">shew</char> <char style="w" strong="H2617">kindness</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H2586">Hanun</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H5176">Nahash</char>, as his <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char> <char style="w" strong="H6213">shewed</char> <char style="w" strong="H2617">kindness</char> unto me. And <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> to <char style="w" strong="H5162">comfort</char> him by the <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char> of his <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char> for his <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char>. And <char style="w" strong="H1732">David’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char> <char style="w" strong="H0935">came</char> into the <char style="w" strong="H0776">land</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H1121">children</char> of <char style="w" strong="H5983">Ammon</char>. <verse eid="2SA 10:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="2SA 10:3" />And the <char style="w" strong="H8269">princes</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H1121">children</char> of <char style="w" strong="H5983">Ammon</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H2586">Hanun</char> their <char style="w" strong="H0113">lord</char>, <char style="w" strong="H5869">Thinkest</char> thou that <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> doth <char style="w" strong="H3513">honour</char> thy <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char>, that he hath <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> <char style="w" strong="H5162">comforters</char> unto thee? hath not <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> <char style="add">rather</char> <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> his <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char> unto thee, <char style="w" strong="H5668">to</char> <char style="w" strong="H2713">search</char> the <char style="w" strong="H5892">city</char>, and to spy it <char style="w" strong="H7270">out</char>, and to <char style="w" strong="H2015">overthrow</char> it?<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">10.3 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Thinkest…: Heb. In thine eyes doth David</char></note> <verse eid="2SA 10:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="2SA 10:4" />Wherefore <char style="w" strong="H2586">Hanun</char> <char style="w" strong="H3947">took</char> <char style="w" strong="H1732">David’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char>, and shaved <char style="w" strong="H1548">off</char> the one <char style="w" strong="H2677">half</char> of their <char style="w" strong="H2206">beards</char>, and cut <char style="w" strong="H3772">off</char> their <char style="w" strong="H4063">garments</char> in the <char style="w" strong="H2677">middle</char>, <char style="add">even</char> to their <char style="w" strong="H8357">buttocks</char>, and sent them <char style="w" strong="H7971">away</char>. <verse eid="2SA 10:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="2SA 10:5" />When they <char style="w" strong="H5046">told</char> <char style="add">it</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char>, he <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> to <char style="w" strong="H7125">meet</char> them, because the <char style="w" strong="H0582">men</char> were <char style="w" stron