  <para style="p">
    <verse number="22" style="v" sid="2SA 11:22" />¶ So the <char style="w" strong="H4397">messenger</char> <char style="w" strong="H3212">went</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H0935">came</char> and <char style="w" strong="H5046">shewed</char> <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> all that <char style="w" strong="H3097">Joab</char> had <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> him for. <verse eid="2SA 11:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="2SA 11:23" />And the <char style="w" strong="H4397">messenger</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char>, Surely the <char style="w" strong="H0582">men</char> <char style="w" strong="H1396">prevailed</char> against us, and came <char style="w" strong="H3318">out</char> unto us into the <char style="w" strong="H7704">field</char>, and we were upon them even unto the <char style="w" strong="H6607">entering</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H8179">gate</char>. <verse eid="2SA 11:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="2SA 11:24" />And the <char style="w" strong="H3384">shooters</char> <char style="w" strong="H3384">shot</char> from off the <char style="w" strong="H2346">wall</char> upon thy <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char>; and <char style="add">some</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char> be <char style="w" strong="H4191">dead</char>, and thy <char style="w" strong="H5650">servant</char> <char style="w" strong="H0223">Uriah</char> the <char style="w" strong="H2850">Hittite</char> is <char style="w" strong="H4191">dead</char> also. <verse eid="2SA 11:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="2SA 11:25" />Then <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto the <char style="w" strong="H4397">messenger</char>, Thus shalt thou <char style="w" strong="H0559">say</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H3097">Joab</char>, Let not this <char style="w