  <para style="p">
    <verse number="26" style="v" sid="2SA 11:26" />¶ And when the <char style="w" strong="H0802">wife</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0223">Uriah</char> <char style="w" strong="H8085">heard</char> that <char style="w" strong="H0223">Uriah</char> her <char style="w" strong="H0376">husband</char> was <char style="w" strong="H4191">dead</char>, she <char style="w" strong="H5594">mourned</char> for her <char style="w" strong="H1167">husband</char>. <verse eid="2SA 11:26" /><verse number="27" style="v" sid="2SA 11:27" />And when the <char style="w" strong="H0060">mourning</char> was <char style="w" strong="H5674">past</char>, <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> and <char style="w" strong="H0622">fetched</char> her to his <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char>, and she became his <char style="w" strong="H0802">wife</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H3205">bare</char> him a <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char>. But the <char style="w" strong="H1697">thing</char> that <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> had <char style="w" strong="H6213">done</char> <char style="w" strong="H3415">displeased</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">11.27 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">displeased: Heb. was evil in the eyes of</char></note><verse eid="2SA 11:27" /></para>
