  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="2SA 12:7" />¶ And <char style="w" strong="H5416">Nathan</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> to <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char>, Thou <char style="add">art</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0376">man</char>. Thus <char style="w" strong="H0559">saith</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>, I <char style="w" strong="H4886">anointed</char> thee <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> over <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>, and I <char style="w" strong="H5337">delivered</char> thee out of the <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char> of <char style="w" strong="H7586">Saul</char>; <verse eid="2SA 12:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="2SA 12:8" />And I <char style="w" strong="H5414">gave</char> thee thy <char style="w" strong="H0113">master’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char>, and thy <char style="w" strong="H0113">master’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H0802">wives</char> into thy <char style="w" strong="H2436">bosom</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H5414">gave</char> thee the <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> and of <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char>; and if <char style="add">that had been</char> too <char style="w" strong="H4592">little</char>, I would moreover have <char style="w" strong="H3254">given</char> unto thee <char style="w" strong="H2007">such</char> and such <char style="w" strong="H2007">things</char>. <verse eid="2SA 12:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="2SA 12:9" />Wherefore hast thou <char style="w" strong="H0959">despised</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1697">commandment</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>, to <char style="w" strong="H6213">do</char> <char style="w" strong="H7451">evil</char> in his <char st