    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="2SA 12:15" />¶ And <char style="w" strong="H5416">Nathan</char> <char style="w" strong="H3212">departed</char> unto his <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char>. And the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H5062">struck</char> the <char style="w" strong="H3206">child</char> that <char style="w" strong="H0223">Uriah’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H0802">wife</char> <char style="w" strong="H3205">bare</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char>, and it was very <char style="w" strong="H0605">sick</char>. <verse eid="2SA 12:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="2SA 12:16" /><char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> therefore <char style="w" strong="H1245">besought</char> <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> for the <char style="w" strong="H5288">child</char>; and <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> <char style="w" strong="H6684">fasted</char>, and went <char style="w" strong="H0935">in</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H7901">lay</char> all <char style="w" strong="H3885">night</char> upon the <char style="w" strong="H0776">earth</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">12.16 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">fasted: Heb. fasted a fast</char></note> <verse eid="2SA 12:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="2SA 12:17" />And the <char style="w" strong="H2205">elders</char> of his <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> <char style="w" strong="H6965">arose</char>, <char style="add">and went</char> to him, to raise him <char style="w" strong="H6965">up</char> from the <char style="w" strong="H0776">earth</char>: but he <char style="w" strong="H0014">would</char> not, neither did he <char style="w" strong="H1262">eat</char> <char style="w" strong="H3899">bread</char> with them. <verse eid="2SA 12:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="2SA 12:18" />And it came to pass on the <char style="w" strong="H7637">seventh<