  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="2SA 18:1" />And <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> <char style="w" strong="H6485">numbered</char> the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> that <char style="add">were</char> with him, and <char style="w" strong="H7760">set</char> <char style="w" strong="H8269">captains</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0505">thousands</char> and <char style="w" strong="H8269">captains</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3967">hundreds</char> over them. <verse eid="2SA 18:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="2SA 18:2" />And <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> sent <char style="w" strong="H7971">forth</char> a third <char style="w" strong="H7992">part</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> under the <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3097">Joab</char>, and a third <char style="w" strong="H7992">part</char> under the <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0052">Abishai</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H6870">Zeruiah</char>, <char style="w" strong="H3097">Joab’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H0251">brother</char>, and a third <char style="w" strong="H7992">part</char> under the <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0863">Ittai</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1663">Gittite</char>. And the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>, I will <char style="w" strong="H3318">surely</char> go <char style="w" strong="H3318">forth</char> with you <char style="w" strong="H0589">myself</char> also. <verse eid="2SA 18:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="2SA 18:3" />But the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">answered</char>, Thou shalt not go <char style="w" strong="H3318">forth</char>: for if we <char style="w" strong="H5127">flee