    <verse number="19" style="v" sid="2SA 18:19" />¶ Then <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> <char style="w" strong="H0290">Ahimaaz</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H6659">Zadok</char>, Let me now <char style="w" strong="H7323">run</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H1319">bear</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="w" strong="H1319">tidings</char>, how that the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> hath <char style="w" strong="H8199">avenged</char> him of his <char style="w" strong="H3027">enemies</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">18.19 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">avenged…: Heb. judged him from the hand, etc</char></note> <verse eid="2SA 18:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="2SA 18:20" />And <char style="w" strong="H3097">Joab</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto him, <char style="w" strong="H0376">Thou</char> shalt not bear <char style="w" strong="H1309">tidings</char> this <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char>, but thou shalt bear <char style="w" strong="H1319">tidings</char> <char style="w" strong="H0312">another</char> <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char>: but this <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> thou shalt bear no <char style="w" strong="H1319">tidings</char>, because the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> is <char style="w" strong="H4191">dead</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">18.20 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">bear tidings this: Heb. be a man of tidings, etc</char></note> <verse eid="2SA 18:20" /><verse number="21" style="v" sid="2SA 18:21" />Then <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> <char style="w" strong="H3097">Joab</char> to <char style="w" strong="H3569">Cushi</char>, <char style="w" strong="H3212">Go</char> <char style="w" strong="H5046">tell</char> the <char 