  <para style="p">
    <verse number="40" style="v" sid="2SA 19:40" />Then the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> went <char style="w" strong="H5674">on</char> to <char style="w" strong="H1537">Gilgal</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H3643">Chimham</char> went <char style="w" strong="H5674">on</char> with him: and all the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char> <char style="w" strong="H5674">conducted</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>, and also <char style="w" strong="H2677">half</char> the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">19.40 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Chimham: Heb. Chimhan</char></note><verse eid="2SA 19:40" /></para>
  <para style="p">
    <verse number="41" style="v" sid="2SA 19:41" />¶ And, behold, all the <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> <char style="w" strong="H0935">came</char> to the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>, Why have our <char style="w" strong="H0251">brethren</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char> stolen thee <char style="w" strong="H1589">away</char>, and have <char style="w" strong="H5674">brought</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>, and his <char style="w" strong="H1004">household</char>, and all <char style="w" strong="H1732">David’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H0582">men</char> with him, over <char style="w" strong="H3383">Jordan</char>? <verse eid="2SA 19:41" /><verse number="42" style="v" sid="2SA 19:42" />And all the <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char> <char style="w" strong="H6030">answered</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>, Because the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="add">is</char> near of <char style="w" strong="H7138">kin</char> to us: wherefore then be ye <char style="w" strong="H2734">angry</char> for this <char style="w" strong="H1697">matter</char>? have we <char style="w" strong="H0398">eaten</char> at <char style="w" strong="H0398">all</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king’s</char> <char style="add">cost</char>? or hath he <char style="w" strong="H5375">given</char> us any <char style="w" strong="H5379">gift</char>? <verse eid="2SA 19:42" /><verse number="43" style="v" sid="2SA 19:43" />And the <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> <char style="w" strong="H6030">answered</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0376">men