  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="2SA 20:1" />And there <char style="w" strong="H7122">happened</char> to be there a <char style="w" strong="H0376">man</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1100">Belial</char>, whose <char style="w" strong="H8034">name</char> <char style="add">was</char> <char style="w" strong="H7652">Sheba</char>, the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1075">Bichri</char>, a <char style="w" strong="H1145">Benjamite</char>: and he <char style="w" strong="H8628">blew</char> a <char style="w" strong="H7782">trumpet</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char>, We have no <char style="w" strong="H2506">part</char> in <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char>, neither have we <char style="w" strong="H5159">inheritance</char> in the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3448">Jesse</char>: <char style="w" strong="H0376">every</char> <char style="w" strong="H0376">man</char> to his <char style="w" strong="H0168">tents</char>, O <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>. <verse eid="2SA 20:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="2SA 20:2" />So every <char style="w" strong="H0376">man</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> went <char style="w" strong="H5927">up</char> from <char style="w" strong="H0310">after</char> <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char>, <char style="add">and</char> <char style="w" strong="H0310">followed</char> <char style="w" strong="H7652">Sheba</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1075">Bichri</char>: but the <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char> <char style="w" strong="H1692">clave</char> unto their <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>, from <char style="w" strong="H3383">Jordan</char> even to <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char>.<verse eid="2SA 20:2" /></para>
  <para style="p">
