eer-sheba</char>. <verse eid="2SA 24:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="2SA 24:8" />So when they had <char style="w" strong="H7751">gone</char> through all the <char style="w" strong="H0776">land</char>, they <char style="w" strong="H0935">came</char> to <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char> at the <char style="w" strong="H7097">end</char> of <char style="w" strong="H8672">nine</char> <char style="w" strong="H2320">months</char> and <char style="w" strong="H6242">twenty</char> <char style="w" strong="H3117">days</char>. <verse eid="2SA 24:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="2SA 24:9" />And <char style="w" strong="H3097">Joab</char> gave <char style="w" strong="H5414">up</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4557">sum</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H4662">number</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> unto the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>: and there were in <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> <char style="w" strong="H8083">eight</char> <char style="w" strong="H3967">hundred</char> <char style="w" strong="H0505">thousand</char> <char style="w" strong="H2428">valiant</char> <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> that <char style="w" strong="H8025">drew</char> the <char style="w" strong="H2719">sword</char>; and the <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char> <char style="add">were</char> <char style="w" strong="H2568">five</char> <char style="w" strong="H3967">hundred</char> <char style="w" strong="H0505">thousand</char> <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char>.<verse eid="2SA 24:9" /></para>
  <para style="p">
